what is the best way to improve my running performance?

ANSWER:
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ANSWER: According to Andrew Huberman, one of the most effective ways to improve your running performance is through high-intensity interval training (HIIT). In episode 20 of the Huberman Lab podcast, he suggests that "the goal for this Friday workout is to really get the heart rate high, do high intensity interval training... A number of different ways you could do that."

Additionally, in episode 49, Huberman mentions that endurance athletes should have a strength and power component to their training. He notes that the interference effect, which suggests that doing both endurance and strength training at the same time might be detrimental, is "probably greatly overblown" for most people.

In general, improving running performance requires a combination of factors, including cardiovascular fitness, muscular strength and endurance, and technique. A well-structured training program that includes a mix of high-intensity interval training, strength exercises, and proper nutrition and recovery strategies can help you achieve your goals.

It's worth noting that the key to HIIT is to start slowly and progress gradually. It's also important to listen to your body and adjust your training plan as needed to avoid injury or burnout.


